PN,38303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F383A1784567930
OL,3,CNatural history museum finishes its
OL,4,Clargest ever redisplay project
OL,6,FBoth were discovered near to Oxford,
OL,7,Fwith archaeologists locating
OL,8,FEustreptospondylus in Summertown, in
OL,9,F1870, and Cumnoria found in Cumnor
OL,10,Fnine years later.
OL,12,FProfessor Irene Tracey, Vice-
OL,13,FChancellor of the University of
OL,14,FOxford, hailed the project's
OL,15,Fcompletion as a "remarkable
OL,16,Fachievement that brings together
OL,17,Fcutting-edge science, outstanding
OL,18,Fcollections and public engagement".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/3
